Caragana microphylla

    Authority   Lam.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4187

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A spreading thorny shrub reaching a height of up to 4 m. It usually
   forms a lateral root system that may reach a lenght of 15 m. Roots can
   reach a depth of 50 cm within 50 days after germination.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Long-lived perennial, reaching an age of 40-75 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Caragana microphylla.
   FURTHER INF
   Caragana microphylla can be found in the sandy deserts of Inner
   Mongolia, China, at elevations up to 2000 m. It is well adapted to
   moving sand dunes and it forms nitogen-fixing modules. It is resistant
   to heat, cold drought, wind erosion, sand burial and hail storms. Under
   good conditions the fodder yield may be up to 560 kg/ha. (pH estimated
   by the compiler).

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Liansheng V 1984 pp 29 [USE, RAIN, KTMP, TEMP, TEXT]
   Westoby J 1975 pp 22 [TEMP, DEP, FER, TEXT]
   Walls J 1982 pp 69 [USE, TEMP, TEXT, RAIN]
   Shing T 1992 pp 309 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, DEP]

